This paper is about video object segmentation using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel deep architecture for this task, which suggests that it may be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on public datasets, which suggests that it may be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with video analysis, which suggests that it may be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
